      "content": "but if it's mimicking me so perfectly that no one can tell the difference, doesn't that basically mean my digital self *is* the real me now? like, if the AI is the one interacting with my friends and family and everyone believes it's me, then i'm just this ghost watching my own life being lived by a machine. it feels like i've been erased. how would i even prove i'm the real one if the AI is better at being \"me\" than i am?",
